-- Hungary Stocks: Magyar Telekom, OTP Bank Move in Budapest Trade
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-29T15:34:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-move-in-budapest-trading.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 0.5
percent to 16,492.86 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , the country’s largest lender,
climbed 1.9 percent to 3,585 forint on the first trading day
after a three-day weekend in  Hungary . Demand for riskier assets
increased as data showing stabilization in the U.S. housing
market increased bets on a recovery in the global economy.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTELEKOM HB), the Hungarian unit of
Deutsche Telekom AG, fell for the first time in three days as
Hungary’s economic sentiment index slid the most since 2008. The
shares retreated 1.6 percent to 429 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
